      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 405: The timer callback checks isShutdown_ without synchronizing with shutdown() clearing reconnectInfos_ and cancelling timers. isShutdown_ is atomic, but a shutdown can occur immediately after the check and before maintainBuckets(), allowing a cancelled/stale timer to schedule new connection work during shutdown. Move the shutdown check under SwarmManager\u0027s mutex or make maintainBuckets() itself return immediately when shutdown is set.\n```suggestion\ninfo.timer-\u003easync_wait([w \u003d weak(), nodeId](const asio::error_code\u0026 ec) {\n    if (ec)\n        return;\n    if (auto shared \u003d w.lock()) {\n        std::lock_guard lock(shared-\u003emutex);\n        if (shared-\u003eisShutdown_)\n            return;\n        // release before calling maintainBuckets(), or add a shutdown guard there\n    }\n    shared-\u003emaintainBuckets({nodeId});\n});\n```",
